text:
Syrian parliamentary: Constitutional Commission proposals are advisory and we rejected any foreign interference
01 Nov 2019, 04:05 by Talk Show
Muhannad al-Haj Ali, a member of the Syrian People's Assembly, said that the new constitutional advisory committee is not mandatory for the government; In a televised address to the Arabs on a week and broadcast on TeN, Ali said that there is significant political progress on the backdrop of the formation of a Syrian government delegation and going to negotiate with dissidents and individuals. Civil society; A member of the Syrian People's Assembly confirmed that the constitution in Syria is being amended based on two options; either a proposal by the People's Assembly or a proposal by the President of the Republic; It has participated in the murder of Syrian citizens, conspired against Syria and financed terrorists;
